<DOCNO> APW19990602.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 12:30:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Recent Fatal U.S. Air Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 10 most recent fatal crashes involving U.S. airliners with  
more than 30 seats -- prior to Tuesday's American Airlines crash in 
Little Rock, Ark.: 

</P>
<P>
	July 17, 1996: A TWA 747 explodes near East Moriches, N.Y.,  
shortly after takeoff, killing 230 people. 
</P>
<P>
	May 11, 1996: A ValuJet DC-9 crashes into the Florida Everglades  
shortly after takeoff, killing 110 people. 
</P>
<P>
	Dec. 20, 1995: An American Airlines 757 crashes in Cali,  
Colombia, upon approach, killing 159 people. 
</P>
<P>
	Oct. 31, 1994: An American Eagle ATR-72 crashes in Roselawn,  
Ind., after circling in icy weather, killing 68 people. 
</P>
<P>
	Sept. 8, 1994: A USAir 737 crashes in Aliquippa, Pa., upon  
approach, killing 132 people. 
</P>
<P>
	July 2, 1994: A USAir DC-9 crashes in Charlotte, N.C., upon  
approach, killing 37 people. 
</P>
<P>
	March 22, 1992: A USAir Fokker 28 crashes in Flushing, N.Y.,  
upon takeoff, killing 27 people. 
</P>
<P>
	March 3, 1991: A United Airlines 737 in Colorado Springs, Colo.,  
crashes on approach, killing 25 people. 
</P>
<P>
	Feb. 1, 1991: A USAir 737 crashes into another plane in Los  
Angeles upon landing, killing 34 people. 
</P>
<P>
	Dec. 3, 1990: A Northwest Airlines DC-9 is struck by another  
plane in Romulus, Mich., while taxiing, killing eight people. 

</P>
<P>
	 *SOURCES: National Transportation Safety Board and Associated  
Press news reports 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
