<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Raiders Sign RB Rashaan Salaam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Free-agent running back Rashaan Salaam is  
the latest former Heisman Trophy winner to join the Oakland 
Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
	The team signed Salaam on Tuesday to a one-year contact worth a  
reported $350,000. He joins fellow Heisman winners Tim Brown, 
Desmond Howard, Andre Ware and Charles Woodson on Oakland's roster. 
</P>
<P>
	``They gave me a chance to put on a uniform again, they gave me  
a locker again,'' the 24-year-old said. ``So we'll just take it 
from there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Salaam didn't play last season because of surgery in August on  
his right ankle. It was the same ankle that kept him out of part of 
the 1997 season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just want to show them I'm healthy and that I'm an  
all-purpose back,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1995 with the Chicago Bears, Salaam rushed for 1,074 yards on  
296 carries with 10 touchdowns. In 31 NFL games, he has rushed for 
1,682 yards with 14 touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
	Salaam, 24, gained 2,055 yards with 24 touchdowns with Colorado  
when he won the Heisman Trophy playing at Colorado in 1994. He was 
the 21st overall selection in the 1995 draft by Chicago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
