<DOCNO> APW19990602.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 12:40:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Adobe Systems To Cut 250 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Some 250 employees will lose their jobs  
at Adobe Systems Inc. this year in a restructuring plan designed to 
increase revenue. 
</P>
<P>
	That number represents 9 percent of Adobe employees worldwide.  
</P>
<P>
	The desktop publishing software company said Wednesday that 40  
percent of the job cuts will come from overseas operations, mainly 
in Edinburgh, Scotland. The savings will be used to increase 
investments in e-business and enhanced marketing programs. 
</P>
<P>
	The San Jose-based Adobe posted 1998 earnings of $105 million on  
revenue of $895 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The company also said it expects to report earnings for the  
second quarter ending June 4 slightly above the range of 62 cents 
to 66 cents a share it had previously estimated. 
</P>
<P>
	A First Call survey of 11 analysts put second-quarter earnings  
at 64 cents a share. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
