<HEADLINE> Fairbank Named Texas Correspondent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Katie DeBo Fairbank, the AP's business  
writer in Texas, has been named correspondent in Fort Worth. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Wednesday by Texas Chief of Bureau  
John Lumpkin. 
</P>
<P>
	Fairbank joined the AP in Indianapolis in 1989 and transferred  
to Columbia, S.C., the following year. She was appointed news 
editor there in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
	Fairbank, 39, transferred to Dallas in 1990 and has been  
business writer since 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	A native of Independence, Kan., Fairbank graduated from Kansas  
State University and worked for the Charleston (S.C.) News and 
Courier and the Dallas Times Herald before joining the AP. She also 
was city editor at the Del Rio (Texas) News-Herald. 
</P>
<P>
	She succeeds Jaime Aron, who was named AP sports writer in  
Dallas. 
  	   	
</P>
