<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gates and Wife Donate $5 Bil. More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Microsoft founder Bill Gates and his wife,  
Melinda, have donated $5 billion to one of their philanthropic 
foundations, making it the third largest in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to announcing the gift Wednesday, the Gates family  
foundation said it, in turn, had given $50 million to the Program 
for Appropriate Technology in Health to help find a vaccine for 
malaria. 
</P>
<P>
	The $5 billion gift of Microsoft Corp. stock to the William H.  
Gates Foundation gives it an asset base of $10 billion. A second 
family charitable organization, the Gates Learning Foundation, has 
assets of $1.3 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	That would make the Gates Foundation, named after and  
administered by Gates' father, the third largest in the country, 
according to recent rankings by The Chronicle of Philanthropy. 
</P>
<P>
	The chronicle lists the Lilly Endowment, in Indianapolis, as the  
largest foundation, with assets of more than $15 billion, followed 
by the Ford Foundation at $10.7 billion. The David and Lucile 
Packard Foundation would be fourth at $9.6 billion, followed by the 
Robert Wood Johnson Foundation at $7.8 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Gates and his wife are estimated to be worth more than $80  
billion. The gift announced Wednesday follows a $3 billion donation 
by the Gateses to their foundation in February. 
</P>
<P>
	The Gates Foundation, started in 1994, provides grants for  
health, population and education projects worldwide. The Gates 
Learning Foundation, launched in 1997, works to spread Internet 
access and computer training. To date, the two organizations have 
made more than $475 million in grants, said spokeswoman Rose Berg. 
</P>
<P>
	Microsoft has suffered from bad publicity in recent years,  
primarily from the government's antitrust lawsuit against the 
software company. Nielsen, however, said the charitable work ``in 
no way whatsoever'' is aimed at countering any negative image. 
</P>
<P>
	``Our work at the foundation has nothing to do with Microsoft  
other than our founder is chairman of Microsoft,'' he said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
