<HEADLINE> Cincinnati Hoop Player Indicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Shawn Myrick, a senior guard at the University  
of Cincinnati last season, was indicted Wednesday on a charge of 
sexual battery. 
</P>
<P>
	Myrick, 22, was accused of having sex with a woman who did not  
give her consent. The Hamilton County grand jury's indictment said 
Myrick knew the woman's ability to control her conduct was 
``substantially impaired.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors said Myrick met the woman at a party that began at a  
club and continued at a hotel where several members of the 
basketball team were staying before a home game in December. The 
woman later accompanied Myrick to his apartment, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	Myrick denied having sex with the woman. DNA test results were  
turned over to the grand jury, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	Myrick, a backup guard from Maysville, Ky., faces up to five  
years in jail if convicted. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
