</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990602.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 19:10:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Police Kill Man After Car Chase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARSIPPANY-TROY HILLS, N.J. (AP) -- Four police officers fired 27  
shots at an unarmed motorist who rammed his car into their cruisers 
during a highway chase Wednesday, killing the man. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver, Stanton Lamont Crew, 31, was struck four times. His  
passenger was struck in the leg. 
</P>
<P>
	Police fired on Crew when he rammed his Camaro into two patrol  
cars that had boxed him in following the chase, Morris County 
Prosecutor John Dangler said. 
</P>
<P>
	``They were in fear of their lives,'' Dangler said.  
</P>
<P>
	Crew was chased when an officer spotted him driving erratically.  
</P>
<P>
	His passenger, Adrienne Lynn Hart, 22, told police that Crew  
said he had no insurance and could not afford to stop. Crew was 
driving with a suspended driver's license and had been issued a 
string of other traffic violations. 
</P>
<P>
	The chase ended after Crew drove off the road onto a patch of  
grass, was boxed in by police and shot. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
