<HEADLINE> The Top Fives in Movies, TV, and Music  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *The Top Fives in Movies, Music    	

</P>
<P>
 *FILMS   	
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' $64.8 million.  
</P>
<P>
	2. ``Notting Hill,'' $27.8 million.  
</P>
<P>
	3. ``The Mummy,'' $12.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	4. ``Entrapment,'' $6.3 million.  
</P>
<P>
	5. ``The Thirteenth Floor,'' $4.3 million.  
</P>
<P>
	(From Exhibitor Relations Co.)  

</P>
<P>
 *HOT FIVE   	
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Livin' la Vida Loca,'' Ricky Martin. C2. (Gold)  
</P>
<P>
	2. ``If You Had My Love,'' Jennifer Lopez.  
</P>
<P>
	3. ``No Scrubs,'' TLC. LaFace. (Gold)  
