<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> `Home Improvement' Goes Out on Top / TV Ratings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tim Allen's ``Home Improvement'' won the battle  
of the farewell episodes. 
</P>
<P>
	The final episode of the long-running ABC comedy was easily last  
week's most-watched show. Much to ABC's surprise and delight, it 
was the fourth-highest rated series finale of the 1990s behind 
``Seinfeld,'' ``Cheers'' and ``The Cosby Show.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Still, NBC scored a narrow prime-time victory for the week and  
won the May ``sweeps'' period, when ratings are watched closely to 
set local advertising rates. 
</P>
<P>
	``Home Improvement'' drew an estimated 35.5 million viewers,  
Nielsen Media Research said Wednesday. The final episode of NBC's 
``Mad About You'' was fourth for the week with nearly 20 million 
viewers. 
</P>
<P>
	The finale of Fox's ``Melrose Place'' had a more lackluster  
showing, finishing in 37th place for the week. 
</P>
<P>
	Only one show -- ``Frasier'' -- from NBC's normally powerful  
Thursday night lineup made Nielsen's top 10 for the week. All were 
repeats as the long summer rerun season begins. 
</P>
<P>
	For the week, NBC had a 7.8 rating and 14 share. ABC and CBS  
both had 7.5 ratings and 14 shares, though ABC had the edge in 
total viewers. Fox had a 5.7 rating and 11 share, and the WB was at 
3.2 and 6. Struggling UPN had a 1.7 rating and 3 share, while Pax 
TV was at 0.7 and 1. 
</P>
<P>
	ABC's ``World News Tonight'' won the evening news competition  
with a 7.1 rating and 17 share. NBC's ``Nightly News'' was at 7.0 
and 16, while the ``CBS Evening News'' was at 5.7 and 13. 
</P>
<P>
	``Nightly News'' claimed victory during May sweeps, with its  
ratings up slightly from last year. 
</P>
<P>
	A rating point represents 994,000 households, or 1 percent of  
the nation's estimated 99.4 million TV homes. The share is the 
percentage of in-use televisions tuned to a given show. 
</P>
<P>
	For the week of May 24-30, the top 10 shows, their networks and  
ratings were ``Home Improvement,'' ABC, 21.6; ``Spin City,'' ABC, 
14.3; ``Law and Order,'' NBC, 13.9; ``Mad About You,'' NBC, ``NYPD 
Blue,'' ABC, 13.5; ``Law and Order'' special, NBC, 11.9; ``Dateline 
NBC-Monday,'' NBC, 10.9; ``Frasier,'' NBC, 10.7; ``ABC Monday Night 
Movie: Cleopatra, Part Two,'' ABC, 10.0; ``Ally McBeal,'' Fox, 
10.0. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
