<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan, Gretzky Mull Legends Golf  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Three retired superstars -- Michael Jordan, Wayne  
Gretzky and John Elway -- will join Fred Couples in an 18-hole 
challenge golf match, Golfweek Magazine reported on its web site 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The program, tentatively titled, ``Legends at Play,'' will  
feature the three retirees from the NBA, NHL and NFL, respectively, 
playing a best-ball format against Couples at Shadow Hawk Golf Club 
in Houston. 
</P>
<P>
	``Its pretty much a done deal,'' Couples was quoted as saying.  
``I think its going to be a really fun thing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Couples not only thought of the idea, but was responsible for  
recruiting the three superstars. He also approached Jack Nicklaus 
Productions about producing the event, which will be televised on 
Fox. 
</P>
<P>
	The contest will be taped around Thanksgiving and will air on  
Christmas Day. There will be no prize money. Any proceeds go to 
charity. 
</P>
<P>
	Couples, an enthusiastic sports fan, said he has played with  
Jordan three or four times and with Elway once, but has never teed 
it up with Gretzky. Asked if the trio filled out his dream 
foursome, Couples smiled and said, ``pretty much. They're guys I'm 
going to love to play with. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of them retired, then another, then another, and it just  
struck me,'' Couples said, describing how the idea came to him. 
``It just struck me as something that made so much sense, seeing 
how much they love golf. Hopefully, it's going to be a fun deal for 
everyone.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
