<HEADLINE> Ex-Florida Governor on Aid Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Former Florida Gov. Buddy MacKay has begun an  
eight-day mission to Central America as an envoy of President 
Clinton to discuss distribution of nearly $1 billion in disaster 
assistance to El Salvador, Honduras, Nicaragua and Guatemala. 
</P>
