<HEADLINE> Mrs. Gore Says Husband is Reserved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Tipper Gore says the vice president is indeed  
a reserved man, and she couldn't be happier about it. 
</P>
<P>
	``I noticed when I met Al that he was reserved, and it's  
something that I liked,'' Mrs. Gore said in an interview last week 
with Oprah Winfrey that was broadcast Wednesday. ``He is reserved 
and that's part of his personality.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Gore said her husband's personality suits her fine.  
</P>
<P>
	``He is funny, he is sexy and he is there when you need him,''  
Mrs. Gore. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Gore said she also likes her husband's prospects as a  
presidential candidate in the 2000 election. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want him to run. I think he's qualified, and I think he'd be  
a terrific president,'' Mrs. Gore said. 
</P>
<P>
	She said the vice president also has been an exemplary father,  
despite the pressures of his job. 
</P>
<P>
	``Every child knows that if they need him, he is there for  
them,'' Mrs. Gore said. ``It doesn't matter what else is going 
on.'' The Gores have three daughters and a son. 
  	   	
</P>
