<HEADLINE> Hanna Named Topeka Correspondent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOPEKA, Kan. (AP) -- John Hanna, who has covered the Kansas  
Legislature for The Associated Press since 1986, has been promoted 
to correspondent in charge of the Topeka bureau. 
</P>
<P>
	He succeeds Lew Ferguson, who is retiring after 29 years as  
correspondent. The appointment was announced Tuesday by Kansas City 
Chief of Bureau Paul Stevens. 
</P>
<P>
	Hanna, 34, is a graduate of the University of Kansas and joined  
the AP in Topeka in 1986. He worked briefly in the Kansas City 
bureau the following year before returning to Topeka. 
</P>
<P>
	Ferguson, 65, has covered nine national political conventions  
for the AP. He joined the news cooperative in 1960 in Oklahoma City 
and was a sports writer in Minneapolis and Kansas City before 
becoming Topeka correspondent in 1970. 
</P>
</TEXT>
