<HEADLINE> Arrest Warrants for Mich St Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Arrest warrants were issued Wednesday  
for Michigan State basketball players Mateen Cleaves and Antonio 
Smith on misdemeanor larceny charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Police pulled over the players on April 14 because their vehicle  
matched the description of one reportedly involved in a store 
theft. 
</P>
<P>
	Michigan State coach Tom Izzo said he hadn't seen the complaint  
or the police reports. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is my understanding that the matter will be dealt with in  
the courts, and after the judicial process runs its course I'll 
take appropriate action,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, 23, also was charged with malicious destruction of  
property. He is accused of breaking open a convenience store cooler 
door lock. 
</P>
<P>
	The crimes are punishable by up to 93 days in jail.  
</P>
<P>
	Cleaves, the team's point guard, led Michigan State to the NCAA  
tournament's Final Four for the first time in 20 years last season. 
He said last month he would return for his senior season. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, the Spartans No. 3 career rebounder, completed his  
eligibility in March. 
</P>
<P>
	Attempts to contact Cleaves and Smith were unsuccessful, but the  
Lansing State Journal reported that the players' lawyer hadn't seen 
the warrants or police reports Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's way too premature to comment,'' lawyer Brian Jeffries  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
