<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hrbaty in French Open Spotlight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Dominik Hrbaty is making a great run at the French  
Open, and he doesn't think much of it. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just play my matches and that is it,'' he said. ``I won some  
matches and I am in the semis, that's all.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 21-year-old Slovak beat Chile's Marcelo Rios on Tuesday in  
the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
	``To me, all matches are the same,'' Hrbaty said. ``Satellite,  
world series, whatever. There is no difference between the matches 
here and other tournaments.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hrbaty, who beat top-ranked Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia in the  
second round, eliminated the ninth-seeded Rios 7-6 (7-4), 6-2, 6-7 
(6-8), 6-3 to set up a semifinal with Andre Agassi. 
</P>
<P>
	And while Paris might be a magical place for some players, it's  
just another city for Hrbaty. 
</P>
<P>
	``All I ever see is the hotel and court, so it makes no  
difference to play in Paris or anywhere else,'' he says. 
</P>
<P>
	Hrbaty, voted best newcomer by his fellow professionals in 1996,  
has taken time to break through. 
</P>
<P>
	His best previous Grand Slam performance came in the 1997  
Australian Open, where he reached the fourth round. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, Hrbaty was in complete control against Rios, who had  
the best clay-court record in 1998 and was one of the tournament 
favorites. 
</P>
<P>
	``He played better than me,'' Rios said. ``I am not that fit  
yet, maybe because I didn't have time to get ready at the beginning 
of the year because of my injury. I had my chance at 3-all, love-40 
(in the first set). I didn't take that chance.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rios fought back to win the third set, thanks to a tiebreaker in  
which Hrbaty made five unforced errors. 
</P>
<P>
	But Hrbaty, who beat Rios and Agassi this year in Key Biscayne,  
Fla., always expected to win. 
</P>
<P>
	``I beat him last time, so I was confident,'' Hrbaty said. ``I  
was thinking during the match, if you beat somebody once, you can 
beat him a second time.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
