<HEADLINE> Another Lawsuit Against Dennis Rodman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Dennis Rodman is being sued again.  
</P>
<P>
	A Kentucky woman has filed suit against the flamboyant former  
NBA player, claiming he assaulted her in the lobby of a Las Vegas 
resort. 
</P>
<P>
	The lawsuit, filed Tuesday in state District Court by Rebecca  
Mardis of Laurel County, Ky., is the latest of several filed 
against Rodman in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
	Mardis alleges Rodman slammed her camera to the floor and lifted  
her into the air in a threatening manner, then laughed at her 
fright. The suit alleges it took place in January in the lobby of 
the MGM Grand Hotel when she tried to take his photo. 
</P>
<P>
	Messages to Rodman's representative at International Creative  
Management were not immediately returned Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mardis seeks $1 million in punitive damages because she alleges  
Rodman has a history of assaulting people. In her lawsuit, Mardis 
alleges assault, battery, intentional infliction of emotional 
distress and property damage. 
</P>
<P>
	On May 19, a casino security guard sued Rodman, accusing him of  
grabbing her breast while she was working at the Las Vegas Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
	Three lawsuits filed in Las Vegas in June 1998 involve other  
allegations about Rodman's behavior in casinos. 
</P>
<P>
	A Las Vegas Hilton employee accused him of grabbing her and  
lifting her off the ground in April 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	A Las Vegas woman accused Rodman of sexually assaulting her in  
April 1998 at the Las Vegas Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
	A craps dealer at The Mirage filed a lawsuit alleging Rodman  
humiliated him at work by rubbing his groin and head. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman played for the Detroit Pistons and Chicago Bulls before  
joining the Los Angeles Lakers for a short stint this year. The 
Lakers waived him in April. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
