<HEADLINE> Al Gore's Uncle Dies at 78 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TRENTON, Tenn. (AP) -- Everett LaFon, an uncle of Vice President  
Al Gore, died Tuesday. He was 78. 
</P>
<P>
	LaFon, a retired firefighter in the west Tennessee city of  
Jackson, died at Gibson County General Hospital. The cause of death 
was not announced. 
</P>
<P>
	LaFon was the brother of the vice president's 86-year-old  
mother, Pauline Gore of Carthage. Jackson was the LaFon family's 
home town when Mrs. Gore was growing up. 
</P>
<P>
	Gore said in a statement that he will remember LaFon as ``a  
loving and proud father, a frank and honest adviser and a dear 
friend.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Survivors include a son and daughter.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
