<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Actress Natalie Portman, born June 9, 1981.  
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Natalie Portman got into show business the  
old-fashioned way. She was sitting in a pizza parlor on New York's 
Long Island when someone offered her a job modeling for a 
children's fragrance. ``It's the classic discovery story,'' she has 
acknowledged. 
</P>
<P>
	She turned down the modeling job because she wanted to pursue  
acting. But the offer helped her get an agent to launch her career. 
She has appeared in several feature films, including Luc Bresson's 
``The Professional,'' and won high marks on Broadway playing the 
lead in ``The Diary of Anne Frank.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She currently stars as Queen Amidala in ``Star Wars: Episode I --  
The Phantom Menace,'' battling alongside Jedi knights to save her 
people from the evil Trade Federation. 
</P>
<P>
	Portman hadn't seen the original ``Star Wars'' trilogy when  
director George Lucas offered her the role in his new film. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was one of the last people in the world to see them,'' she  
said. ``I was the only one on the set who didn't freak out when 
they saw R2D2 for the first time. I think it probably helped me not 
to be caught up in the phenomenon.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Up Next:* Portman will star with Susan Sarandon in Wayne Wang's  
``Anywhere But Here,'' the story of a mother and daughter who must 
come to terms with their volatile relationship in the midst of a 
move from Michigan to Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:*''Acting probably is making me grow up faster than I  
normally would because I'm around adults so much of the time. I'm 
friends with people much older than me, but they're all quite 
intent on maintaining my innocence.'' 

</P>
