<HEADLINE> Heinz Buys Foodservice Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- The H.J. Heinz Co. expanded its huge global  
single-serve business by acquiring Thermo Pac Inc. of Georgia and 
Serv-A-Portion of Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deals announced Wednesday were not disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Thermo Pac of Stone Mountain employs 160 at a factory in Atlanta  
manufacturing single-serve packets of food to foodservice and 
grocery customers throughout the U.S. It had been a privately-held 
company. 
</P>
<P>
	Serv-A-Portion specializes in manufacturing jams and sauces,  
exporting more than 85 percent of its products to European markets 
from its factory in Turnhout, where 110 people work. It acquired 
Serv-A-Portion from Medeol, the consumer products division of 
agro-foods company Eridania Beghin-Say. 
</P>
<P>
	Heinz already owns Portion Pac Inc., the U.S's largest  
manufacturer of single-serve products for the nation's foodservice 
industry. 
</P>
<P>
	Pittsburgh-based Heinz operates in 200 countries and has nearly  
$10 billion in sales. 
  	   	
</P>
